1. Linear Search
Definition

Checks each element one by one until the target is found.

Time Complexity
Best Case: O(1)
Average Case: O(n)
Worst Case: O(n)
Space Complexity
O(1)
Java Code
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int[] arr = new int[n];

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
            arr[i] = sc.nextInt();

        int key = sc.nextInt();

        int found = -1;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (arr[i] == key) {
                found = i;
                break;
            }
        }

        if (found != -1)
            System.out.println("Found at index " + found);
        else
            System.out.println("Not Found");
    }
}
Input

5
10 20 30 40 50
30

Output
Found at index 2


